A vintage 1960s style illustration depicting a sprawling spider web of interconnected nodes, where a central hub represents a customer surrounded by radiating threads connecting to various symbolic elements: a factory, a delivery truck, a telephone, filing cabinets, and small human figures in mid-century business attire. The color palette features muted teals, warm oranges, and cream tones typical of retro corporate illustrations. The composition uses a bird's-eye view perspective, with the web pattern creating an organic yet systematic feel, emphasizing the interconnected nature of all customer touchpoints. Subtle paper texture overlay gives it an aged advertisement quality.
